# Hero copy — cyan line rule

In **Layout Studio → Site bounds** (yellow + cyan guides):

| Guide | CSS | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| **Yellow** | `--beiza-site-padding-x` | Site boundary — nav, footer, full-width sections |
| **Cyan** | `--beiza-site-padding-x` + `--beiza-content-indent` | **Hero copy start line** |

## Rule

**All marketing hero headlines and body copy start on the cyan line** — whether the block is left- or right-aligned.

- **Left hero:** first character aligns with the **left cyan** guide.
- **Right hero:** the copy block’s **right edge** aligns with the **right cyan** guide (`siteHeroCopyBlockRight` + `ml-auto`).

Do **not** add extra `pl-*` / `pr-*` / `sm:pl-8` / `lg:pl-14` on hero copy — that breaks the guides.

## Code (use these — do not invent padding)

| Export | File |
|--------|------|
| `siteHeroCopyInsetX` | `src/lib/siteLayout.ts` — hero shell horizontal inset |
| `siteHeroCopyBlockLeft` | left-aligned headline block |
| `siteHeroCopyBlockRight` | right-aligned headline block (Heritage default) |
| `siteHeroContentRow` | full-bleed hero row inside `FullBleedHero` |
| `HERO_CONTENT_CLASS` | `src/lib/brandImages.ts` — same cyan inset |

Studio offsets (`copyOffsetX` / `copyOffsetY` from hero layout studio) are **additional** nudges in vw/vh on top of the cyan anchor — not a substitute for it.

## Pages

- `/home` — `Hero.tsx`
- `/events` — `FullBleedHero` + `siteHeroCopyBlockLeft`
- `/heritage`, `/farewell` — `FullBleedHero` + `siteHeroCopyBlockLeft` / `siteHeroCopyBlockRight`

Heritage (`/farewell`) is the visual reference when tuning cyan indent in studio.
